message.text:
#Hiragana Master
Say it Together! Basic Japanese Words in Japanese Alphabetical Order.
Today's Word is "ME" MEGANE　#nihongo
日本の単語を五十音順にわかりやすく紹介！「め」がね（眼鏡、Glasses）
http://eng.nihongodecarenavi.jp/jpn/entry_7454.html

Do you wear Megane (glasses) or have ever used it? I'm sure many people do!（It is said one in two Japanese do...and I DO!)

These days, Megane has been evolving so rapidly, and it is not only used for its original use anymore, that is to see something clearly.
It is also used as the fashionable items(some even have no lenses), as the eye-health items (protecting your eyes from PC screen light, pollen or dust), or even as a device!

Maybe in the near future, we could see the future through Megane!?!? Will see!

みなさん、めがねをかけていますか？かけたことありますか？（日本人の２人１人はかけてるとか？私はかけています！）
最近のめがね・・・物を見るためだけじゃないですよね。
おしゃれのため、目の健康のため、最近ではＰＣみたいな役割まで！もしかしたら近い将来、未来も見えたりして？？

message.text:
<KANJI Quiz!>
How do you read the Kanji "城"(castle)？ Choose the answer!
1. しろ（shiro) 2. しゃく(shaku) 3. よろい(yoroi)
http://www.anime-manga.jp/KanjiGame/Samurai/

Do you know how many castles were there in Japan at its peak?
It is said that there used to be more than 25,000 castles, and now it downs to 12 which exist as it was. 

Japanese castles were/are often decorated with fish-shaped ornaments called "Shachihoko", an imaginary creature. What do you think the meaning of placing "Shachihoko" on the roof?

「城」の読み方はどれ？
日本には、一番多いときでどのくらい「城」があったと思いますか？今昔のままで残っているものは１２！ととても少ないですが、実は！ピーク時には25,000以上の城があったといわれています。

城の屋根にはよく「しゃちほこ」という魚の形をした想像上の動物が飾られています。
なぜ「しゃちほこ」を飾るか、わかりますか？

message.text:
Snowing in Tokyo today! In such a weather, don't you think watching Ramen documentary movie would be the good way to warm your body up?
今日の東京は雪！こんなに日はラーメン映画（！！）でも見て温まりませんか？

Toronto (Canada)：Jan. 22 [Japanese Film Screening] "The God of Ramen"
トロント:1/22 ドキュメンタリー映画『ラーメンより大切なもの』（印南貴史監督、2013年）
http://jftor.org/event/epicure/

A documentary about a beloved ramen chef and his ramen shop in Ikebukuro, Tokyo. 
People wait in line for over two hours for just one bowl of ramen at the legendary ramen shop “East Ikebukuro Taishoken.” What makes his ramen so special? Why is Taishoken beloved by so many?
Check out the secret of the ramen chef, and warm your body and soul up!

池袋にある伝説のラーメン屋「東池袋大勝軒」に迫ったドキュメンタリー映画を上映。１杯のラーメンに２時間も行列ができる…その秘密は何なのでしょう？
映画を見て心も体も温まりましょう♪
